text: The 1991–92 Combined Counties Football League season was the 14th in the history of the Combined Counties Football League, a football competition in England. The league was won by Farnham Town for the second season in succession, who subsequently left to join the Isthmian League. ==Clubs== The league was increased from 17 clubs to 19 after two new clubs joined: *Ditton, joining from the Surrey Premier League. *Viking Sports, joining from the Hellenic League Division One. ===League table=== ==References== ==External links== * Combined Counties League Official Site 1991-92 Category:1991–92 in English football leagues
